TITLE: Defining Plugin Interface Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript interface and type definitions for a Capacitor plugin showing three different method signatures: void return, value return, and callback methods. Includes type definitions for callback ID and data structures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v5/plugins/creating-plugins/method-types.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export type CallbackID = string;

export interface MyData {
  data: string;
}

export type MyPluginCallback = (message: MyData | null, err?: any) => void;

export interface MyPlugin {
  method1(): Promise<void>;
  method2(): Promise<MyData>;
  method3(callback: MyPluginCallback): Promise<CallbackID>;
}
```

