TITLE: Defining HTTP Request Options Interface - Capacitor - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure of the HttpOptions interface and its properties for configuring HTTP requests using Capacitor. Essential properties include url, method, headers, timeout settings, request data, and additional web fetch configuration. The table describes expected data types, platform-specific constraints (notably for complex data types on iOS/Android), and how each option modifies request behavior. Dependencies include the Capacitor runtime and, in some cases, patched fetch/XHR calls. Inputs are strongly typed, with outputs determined by the configured responseType and dataType.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v6/apis/http.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface HttpOptions {
  url: string; // The URL to send the request to.
  method?: string; // HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.) Defaults to 'GET'.
  params?: HttpParams; // URL parameters to append to the request
  data?: any; // Payload. On mobile, must be string/JSON; complex types require base64 serialization.
  headers?: HttpHeaders; // HTTP headers
  readTimeout?: number; // Timeout for reading additional data (ms)
  connectTimeout?: number; // Timeout for initial connection (ms)
  disableRedirects?: boolean; // Disable automatic HTTP redirects
  webFetchExtra?: RequestInit; // Extra web fetch init options
  responseType?: HttpResponseType; // How to parse the response; ignored for JSON content-type
  shouldEncodeUrlParams?: boolean; // If false, disables automatic URL param encoding (default: true)
  dataType?: 'file' | 'formData'; // Indicates if data was converted on the native layer
}
```

