TITLE: Creating a Basic Echo Plugin in Swift
DESCRIPTION: Defines a simple Capacitor iOS plugin named `EchoPlugin` in Swift. It extends `CAPPlugin` and includes an `echo` method exposed to Objective-C via `@objc`. This method retrieves a string value named "value" from the plugin call (`CAPPluginCall`), provides a default empty string if not found, and returns the received value back to the JavaScript caller within a dictionary using `call.resolve()`.
