TITLE: Unsafely Accessing Dictionary Value Directly in Capacitor Plugin (Swift)
DESCRIPTION: This Swift snippet shows an incorrect approach to checking for a value's existence by accessing the `call.options` dictionary directly. This is problematic because if the value associated with the key `"foo"` is `NSNull`, the condition `call.options["foo"] != nil` evaluates to true (as `NSNull` is an object, not `nil`), potentially leading to unexpected behavior or runtime errors if the code inside the block assumes a non-null value of a specific type. It's recommended to use type-specific accessors like `getString` instead.
