TITLE: Accessing Data from PluginCall in Capacitor Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to read various data types from the PluginCall object in a Capacitor plugin method using Java. It pulls strings, objects, and booleans using convenience methods and validates required fields before resolving or rejecting. It depends on the Capacitor Android runtime, with dependencies on PluginCall and JSObject. Parameters include 'yourName', 'address', 'isAwesome', and a required 'id' field.
