TITLE: Running Capacitor Event Listeners within Angular's NgZone (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to handle Capacitor plugin event listeners, such as 'networkStatusChange' from the Network plugin, within an Angular component. Since these listeners execute outside Angular's NgZone, the callback logic must be wrapped in 'this.ngZone.run()' to ensure Angular's change detection is triggered and UI updates reflect the new state (e.g., network status). This requires injecting 'NgZone' from '@angular/core' into the component constructor and utilizing a Capacitor plugin like '@capacitor/network'.
