TITLE: Checking Permission Status using CLLocationManager - Swift
DESCRIPTION: This method 'checkPermissions' maps the authorization state from CLLocationManager to a plugin-friendly string status ('prompt', 'denied', 'granted'), and returns it using call.resolve. It demonstrates reading native framework states, mapping them to custom states, and returning structured results. Dependencies include CoreLocation and Capacitor; must be used within a CAPPlugin subclass.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v6/plugins/creating-plugins/ios-guide.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
@objc override func checkPermissions(_ call: CAPPluginCall) {
    let locationState: String

    switch CLLocationManager.authorizationStatus() {
    case .notDetermined:
        locationState = "prompt"
    case .restricted, .denied:
        locationState = "denied"
    case .authorizedAlways, .authorizedWhenInUse:
        locationState = "granted"
    @unknown default:
        locationState = "prompt"
    }

    call.resolve(["location": locationState])
}
```

