TITLE: Exporting Dynamic Capacitor Configuration - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code dynamically exports a Capacitor configuration object based on the value of process.env.NODE_ENV. It defines a shared baseConfig, then conditionally augments it with iOS scheme and Android flavor properties depending on whether NODE_ENV is 'qa' or not. This enables seamless switching between environments using environment variables. Prerequisites: The '@capacitor/cli' package and environment variable setup (e.g., via cross-env or shell).
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v6/main/guides/environment-specific-configurations.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { CapacitorConfig } from '@capacitor/cli';

let config: CapacitorConfig;

const baseConfig: CapacitorConfig = {
  appId: 'io.ionic.starter',
  appName: 'My App',
  webDir: 'build',
  bundledWebRuntime: false,
};

switch (process.env.NODE_ENV) {
  case 'qa':
    config = {
      ...baseConfig,
      ios: {
        scheme: 'App QA',
      },
      android: {
        flavor: 'qa',
      },
    };
    break;
  default:
    config = {
      ...baseConfig,
      ios: {
        scheme: 'App',
      },
      android: {
        flavor: 'dev',
      },
    };
    break;
}

export default config;
```

