TITLE: Specifying ProGuard Keep Rules for Plugin Code - Plaintext
DESCRIPTION: These ProGuard directives are intended for the proguard-rules.pro file in an Android project. The first rule tells ProGuard to keep all classes in the com.mythirdpartyplugin package; the second rule keeps all public classes that extend com.getcapacitor.Plugin, effectively disabling code shrinking for these plugin classes. This prevents issues where ProGuard removes necessary classes or methods required at runtime by plugins.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/main/android/troubleshooting.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
-keep class com.mythirdpartyplugin.** { *; }
```

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
-keep public class * extends com.getcapacitor.Plugin
```

