TITLE: Implementing ScreenOrientation Class in Java for Android
DESCRIPTION: This class handles the core functionality for screen orientation detection, providing a method to get the current orientation type by mapping Android rotation values to orientation types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/docs/plugins/tutorial/implementing-for-android.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
package io.ionic.cap.plugin.plugins.ScreenOrientation;

import android.view.Surface;
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;

public class ScreenOrientation {
   private AppCompatActivity activity;

   public ScreenOrientation(AppCompatActivity activity) {
       this.activity = activity;
   }

   public String getCurrentOrientationType() {
       int rotation = activity.getWindowManager().getDefaultDisplay().getRotation();
       return fromRotationToOrientationType(rotation);
   }

   private String fromRotationToOrientationType(int rotation) {
       switch (rotation) {
           case Surface.ROTATION_90:
               return "landscape-primary";
           case Surface.ROTATION_180:
               return "portrait-secondary";
           case Surface.ROTATION_270:
               return "landscape-secondary";
           default:
               return "portrait-primary";
       }
   }
}
```

