TITLE: Implementing Permission Checks in Swift for Capacitor iOS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to implement the checkPermissions method to return current permission status for location services
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v5/plugins/creating-plugins/ios-guide.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
@objc override func checkPermissions(_ call: CAPPluginCall) {
    let locationState: String

    switch CLLocationManager.authorizationStatus() {
    case .notDetermined:
        locationState = "prompt"
    case .restricted, .denied:
        locationState = "denied"
    case .authorizedAlways, .authorizedWhenInUse:
        locationState = "granted"
    @unknown default:
        locationState = "prompt"
    }

    call.resolve(["location": locationState])
}
```

