TITLE: Initializing Watch App Main Entry Point (Swift)
DESCRIPTION: This Swift code defines the main entry point for the watchOS application using SwiftUI. It imports necessary frameworks (SwiftUI, WatchConnectivity, iOS_capWatch_watch), sets up the main App structure, and initializes the `CapWatchContentView` provided by the plugin. It also configures and activates the WatchConnectivity session for the watch app when the view appears.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v6/apis/watch.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
import SwiftUI
import WatchConnectivity
import iOS_capWatch_watch

@main
struct watchddgg_Watch_AppApp: App {
    var body: some Scene {
        WindowGroup {
            CapWatchContentView()
                .onAppear {
                    assert(WCSession.isSupported(), "This sample requires Watch Connectivity support!")
                    WCSession.default.delegate = WatchViewModel.shared
                    WCSession.default.activate()
                }
        }
    }
}
```

