TITLE: Implementing Orientation Lock Logic in ScreenOrientation Class (Swift)
DESCRIPTION: This public Swift function in the `ScreenOrientation` class locks the device orientation to the specified `orientationType`. It converts the type string to mask and integer values, sets the device orientation using `UIDevice.current.setValue`, attempts the rotation, and calls a completion handler with the orientation mask. Operations are dispatched to the main queue asynchronously.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v5/plugins/tutorial/implementing-for-ios.md#2025-04-23_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
public func lock(_ orientationType: String, completion: @escaping (UIInterfaceOrientationMask) -> Void) {
  DispatchQueue.main.async {
    let mask = self.fromOrientationTypeToMask(orientationType)
    let orientation = self.fromOrientationTypeToInt(orientationType)
    UIDevice.current.setValue(orientation, forKey: "orientation")
    UINavigationController.attemptRotationToDeviceOrientation()
    completion(mask)
  }
}
```

