TITLE: Dynamically Exporting Capacitor Config for Multiple Environments - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Implements logic in capacitor.config.ts to export different Capacitor configuration objects depending on the NODE_ENV environment variable. Imports types, defines a base config, then returns a customized object with iOS and Android settings for 'qa' or the default environment. Accepts NODE_ENV as input, outputs the appropriate config object for runtime use.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/main/guides/environment-specific-configurations.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { CapacitorConfig } from '@capacitor/cli';

let config: CapacitorConfig;

const baseConfig: CapacitorConfig = {
  appId: 'io.ionic.starter',
  appName: 'My App',
  webDir: 'build',
  bundledWebRuntime: false,
};

switch (process.env.NODE_ENV) {
  case 'qa':
    config = {
      ...baseConfig,
      ios: {
        scheme: 'App QA',
      },
      android: {
        flavor: 'qa',
      },
    };
    break;
  default:
    config = {
      ...baseConfig,
      ios: {
        scheme: 'App',
      },
      android: {
        flavor: 'dev',
      },
    };
    break;
}

export default config;
```

