TITLE: Accessing Input Data in a Capacitor Android Plugin Method in Java
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates retrieving various data types (String, JSObject, Boolean) from the `PluginCall` instance within a plugin method. It utilizes methods like `getString`, `getObject`, `getBoolean` with default values and shows how to check for the existence of a specific key ('id') using `call.getData().has()` before potentially rejecting the call.
