TITLE: Using Camera API in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to capture/select a photo using Capacitor's Camera API with options for quality, editing and result type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v2/apis/camera.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Plugins, CameraResultType } from '@capacitor/core';

const { Camera } = Plugins;

async takePicture() {
  const image = await Camera.getPhoto({
    quality: 90,
    allowEditing: true,
    resultType: CameraResultType.Uri
  });
  // image.webPath will contain a path that can be set as an image src.
  // You can access the original file using image.path, which can be
  // passed to the Filesystem API to read the raw data of the image,
  // if desired (or pass resultType: CameraResultType.Base64 to getPhoto)
  var imageUrl = image.webPath;
  // Can be set to the src of an image now
  imageElement.src = imageUrl;
}
```

