TITLE: Using Common Variables for Dependencies in Android App Build File
DESCRIPTION: This diff demonstrates updating the `dependencies` block in `android/app/build.gradle` to use the common variables for AndroidX and testing library versions. It also highlights the necessary change from single quotes to double quotes to enable Groovy variable interpolation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ionic-team/capacitor-docs/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-v3/main/updating/2-0.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
 dependencies {
     implementation fileTree(include: ['*.jar'], dir: 'libs')
-    implementation 'androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.0.0'
+    implementation "androidx.appcompat:appcompat:$androidxAppCompatVersion"
     implementation project(':capacitor-android')
-    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.12'
-    androidTestImplementation 'androidx.test.ext:junit:1.1.1'
-    androidTestImplementation 'androidx.test.espresso:espresso-core:3.1.0'
+    testImplementation "junit:junit:$junitVersion"
+    androidTestImplementation "androidx.test.ext:junit:$androidxJunitVersion"
+    androidTestImplementation "androidx.test.espresso:espresso-core:$androidxEspressoCoreVersion"
     implementation project(':capacitor-cordova-android-plugins')

```

